FacebookClient
==============

Low-Fi client for the Facebook API


=== Install

- copy sample facebook_client.yml to the config directory
- update facebook_client.yml with your app info
- use "rake set_fb_app_properties" to set your app properties

=== Usage

* API Calls

fb = FacebookClient::Service.new(:api_key => 'api-key', :secret => 'secret')
fb.call 'users.getInfo', :session_key => 'session-key', :uids => 'user-id', :fields => 'birthday'


* Routing

Use the :canvas parameter to route to the facebook canvas url, for example:

url_for(:controller=>'users',:canvas=>true) 
# => apps.facebook.com/canvasname/users

url_for(:controller=>'users',:canvas=>false) 
# => my.callbackurl.com/users


=== Conflicts

By default the asset host is set to the callback_url




